--TASK 3 SQL 

ðŸ”¹ Migration Scripts

1. Export from MySQL

# Export database from MySQL
mysqldump -u root -p mydb > mydb.sql

2. Convert schema for PostgreSQL

LOAD DATABASE
     FROM mysql://root:password@localhost/mydb
     INTO postgresql://postgres:password@localhost/mydb

 WITH include drop, create tables, create indexes, reset sequences

 SET work_mem to '16MB', maintenance_work_mem to '512 MB';

3. Import into PostgreSQL (if using dump)

psql -U postgres -d mydb -f mydb.sql

